node.text: @shirin.abedinirad “Tide” in Australia Swell Sculpture Biennale / September 2019

“Greatnes always left scars... temptation only ... opened more doors. But all we ever wanted, was just another way out.” _____________________
@_deryadilara_ ✍🏻

“I was both in awe and in utter fear of her...”
__  @_deryadilara_ ✍🏻 @thedigitalaphrodite 💙

“I knew how I could get you. I knew what to say and how to act – I’d been that woman for years, flirting my way around lost souls with the tips of my red polished fingers.  But I was tired. I wanted to show your stupid social soul who I really was… behind all these velvet curtains.”
✍🏻 @_deryadilara_

“I didn't resist. 
I didn't fight.
This time, 
I just let the words flow in my ears 
I just digested every fibre of the soft harshness of their reality 
It didn't matter what was right. 
It didn’t matter who was there.
I was alone again.”
____
✍🏻 @_deryadilara_

"It comes out mostly at night,... the wildness. It pushes through into the present, regardless of manner or time. At the most inopportune moment, she is there screaming for pleasure, pain, and attention. I wonder... where she take us tonight?”
___
✍🏻 @_deryadilara_
